          "stimulus": "<h4><span style=\"color:#8b4513;\"><strong>Task 1: Academic Style Basics</strong></span></h4>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"><strong>Choose the correct answer to complete the rules for good academic style</strong></span></p>\n",
          "template": "<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_3166S\" style=\"display: none;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_7898S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3120S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><strong>{{response}}</strong><span id=\"cke_bm_3166E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\">One of the most important objectives of good academic style&nbsp;to keep your writing clear and <span id=\"cke_bm_3166S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3120S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_3166E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>. This means getting your ideas across in a comprehensible form, without using unnecessary words. You should also avoid using unnecessary information.&nbsp;Good critical writing means knowing what to keep and what to cut out. You have a limited number of words for your assessments - Use them well!</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_3166S\" style=\"display: none;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_7898S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3120S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><strong>{{response}}</strong><span id=\"cke_bm_3166E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\">A wide range of vocabulary is important, but you not all words are suitable for academic writing. It is important&nbsp;to avoid informal language, especially <span id=\"cke_bm_3600S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3166S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3120S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_3166E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> expressions and slang. Academic writing also requires standard spelling and full forms (e.g \"do not\" should be used in place of \"don't\").</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_3166S\" style=\"display: none;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_7898S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3120S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><strong>{{response}}</strong><span id=\"cke_bm_3166E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\">In your writing you need to have a clear argument, which develops logically. To&nbsp;develop a&nbsp;{{response}}&nbsp;argument, where ideas connect and build on each other, structure is important. Focus on how your sentences are arranged in each paragraph, how paragraphs link to each other, and how the different sections of your reports and essays are organised. Does the organisation or your writing help the reader follow your ideas?</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_3166S\" style=\"display: none;\"><span id=\"cke_bm_7898S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3120S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span><strong>{{response}}</strong><span id=\"cke_bm_3166E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.1em;\">Finally, academic writing must be&nbsp;{{response}}&nbsp;and based on evidence. In order for your ideas to be taken seriously, you need to show that they are supported by experts and serious research.&nbsp;However, as different viewpoints exist, it is also important to be <span id=\"cke_bm_9423S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3600S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3166S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> <span id=\"cke_bm_3120S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_3166E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span> when presenting ideas.&nbsp;</span></p>\n",
